The red dye Sudan I has been found in a pepper sauce made by the Heinz Meiweiyuan Food Co. based in Guangzhou, capital of southern China's Guangdong province.
China launched a food safety inspection when Sudan I was detected in a pepper sauce produced by a subsidiary of American company Heinz, Heinz-Meiweiyuan Food Co., Ltd. in southern China's Guangzhou city earlier this month.
The agency found the dye in products of companies such as Schweppes, Coca Cola and Unilever.
Sudan-I is traditionally used for coloring solvents, oils, waxes, petrol and shoe and floor polishes.
